<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-08-25T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-08-25T14:00:00-05:00" n="559" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d559">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">817.113/362: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Dawson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-08-25T13:00:00-06:00">August 25, 1934—1
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 3 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>148. Department’s telegram No. 50, August 17, 4 p.m. Note received today
                            from Ministry of Foreign Affairs acknowledging receipt of my
                            communication informing it of change in procedure for the issuance of
                            licenses for exportation of arms and munitions from the United States to
                            Nicaragua.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Dawson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>